The paper discusses data profiling techniques and their application in ensuring the reliability and proper function of data-driven applications. It introduces a new data-profiling primitive called data invariants, which models arithmetic relationships involving multiple numerical attributes within a dataset. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the database (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories.
